    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>B3 single spectral line observation of 110.8655155 GHz in SGR_B2</prj:name>
        <prj:note>In our gas-grain chemical model, we have shown that gas phase production of CHDCN− anion is significant. Rate coefficient for the formation of CHDCN− was unknown till date. We have carried out quantum chemical calculations to find out the rate coefficients for the formation and destruction of CHDCN− in the gas phase. Radiative electron attachment is found to be the major production route of CHDCN− anion in the gas phase while mutual neutralization serves as the main destruction route for this anion. Peak abundance of gas
phase CHDCN− found by our model is ∼ 1 × 10−10 . Peak cloumn density of CHDCN− anion for nH = 2745.07 cm−3 , AV =5 is 1.04 × 1012 . We also have carried our quantum chemical calculation to find out different rotational transitions of this speies. Armed with our chemical modeling as well as the information about the rotational transitions, we are proposing to observe this species with ALMA.

Sgr B2 is a massive star-forming region. It is well known for its abundance of molecular species and has been the target of many searches for complex molecules. We want to observe the gas phase CHDCN− by observing line transition in 110.8655155 GHz. 
</prj:note>
