        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We want to observe SGR B2 (RA: 17h47m20.4s, δ : −28d23′ 07.08′′ ) in spectral line mode to search for CHDCN− . The central frequency of CHDCN− emission line is 110.8655155 GHz. Since SGR B2 have source velocity of 61.6 km/s at a red shift of z = 0.000205497, the corresponding observing frequency will be 110.84273764994116 GHz. We will use 3th band with 58.594 MHz (158 km/s) bandwidth and 35.278 kHz (0.095 km/s) channel resolution. Since we opt for finest resolution bandwidth (35.278 kHz) for our observation and we want atleast 12 mJy sensitivity per pointing (which is equivalent
to 7.46389K). By using ALMA time estimator, we find 22.01m total on source time is required to achieve our intended sensitivity. We will also need 19.18m calibration time and 15.97m observation overhead. So, in total, we will need 28.58m ALMA 12 m array time. But, since ALMA 12 m array multiplication factor is 3, we will need 5.24 m (total ACA+TP time) in total.Since the size of SGR B2 is &gt; 4 arcmin, we will need complementary ACA observation to detect large scale structure of the source. We understand that full structure of SGR B2 will not be detected with single scan observation even if we observe with ACA but detection of structure of the order of 20 arcsec, which is detectable by ACA, will be sufficient for our scientific purpose.

</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
