    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>It has long been suggested that CH2CN− (cyanomethyl anion) might be a carrier of one of the many
poorly characterized diffuse interstellar bands. Our chemical model predicts that the one of the
deuterated form (CHDCN− ) of cyanomethy anion is reasonably abundant around the dense region of
the molecular cloud. Based on our quantum chemical calculation, we have predicted that rotational
transitions of CHDCN− anion should be easily detected by ALMA. We are proposing to observe
110.8655155 GHz line frequency (3rd band of ALMA) of the gas phase CHDCN− anion.</prp:abstract>
